results.notes:
'Flood Extent' shows the extent of the largest recorded historical flood event or estimated 1% Annual Exceedance Probability (AEP) design flood event. Quality of data varies from high quality with floodmapping from detailed flood studies (eg Barwon River) to low quality where flood extent has been estimated subjectively from geological maps (eg Hovells Creek upstream of Lara).

The areas shown are considered to be designated as being liable to flooding in accordance with Regulation 802 of the Building Regulations 2006. 

Although all due care has been taken to ensure that these data are correct, no warranty is expressed or implied by the City of Greater Geelong in their use. Geographic Coordinate System: GCS_WGS_1984.

organization.description: The Australian Government Bioregional Assessment Programme is a collaboration between the Department of the Environment and Energy, the Bureau of Meteorology, CSIRO and Geoscience Australia.  The Programme seeks to better understand the potential impacts of coal seam gas and large coal mining developments on water resources and water-related assets. It is one of a number of actions undertaken by the Australian Government to strengthen the science underpinning decision making on coal seam gas and large coal mining developments.

results.name: edd21ff8-0e42-49d9-a5f1-c619757860ac
results.notes:
## **Abstract** 

This dataset was derived by the Bioregional Assessment Programme. The parent datasets are identified in the Lineage field in this metadata statement. The processes undertaken to produce this derived dataset are described in the History field in this metadata statement.



This data file contains surface water allocation information for the different catchments in the Galilee subregion preliminary assessment extent (PAE). It describes permit types, location and owner of individual permit.

## **Purpose** 

It has been designed to extract water accounts (permit type and total allocation) in different river catchments within the Galilee subregion.

## **Dataset History** 

The Australia's River Basins 1997 dataset (GUID: d4561e86-2d13-4dcb-bf9e-aae75ba4850c) was spatially joined to the QLD DNRM Licence Locations Linked to Cadastre Plan - Clipped to GAL PAE dataset (GUID: da3fe07d-99f6-4efa-970a-6f445ebd16cc) and attribute table exported as an Excel worksheet: 'GAL_DNRM_SWLic_LinkedToLocation'



A pivot table was exported as a summary ('Summary') showing the volume (ML) and number of entitlements per water year for each 'Purpose'.



A pivot table (PivotT) was created from the output worksheet to summarise the count and volume (ML) of nominal water entitlements per catchment, per year.

Field List - Authorised (Purpose), NominalEntitlementPerWaterYearML

Column Labels - Values

Row Labels - Authorised

Values - Sum of NominalEntitlementPerWaterYearML, Count of NominalEntitlementPerWaterYearML



A second pivot table was created ('PivotT') and exported as a summary ('Summary II") showing the number and volume (ML) of entitlements per water year for each catchment.



Field List - NominalEntitlementPerWaterYearML, AssetName, BNAME

Colum Labels - Values

Row Label - BNAME, AssetName

Values - Count of NominalEntitlementPerWaterYearML, Sum of NominalEntitlementPerWaterYearML

## **Dataset Citation** 

Bioregional Assessment Programme (XXXX) Summary Analysis of QLD DNRM Licence Locations Linked to Cadastre Plan - Clipped to GAL PAE v01. Bioregional Assessment Derived Dataset. Viewed 11 April 2016, http://data.bioregionalassessments.gov.au/dataset/edd21ff8-0e42-49d9-a5f1-c619757860ac.

results.notes: During April and May 1960, a Cessna aircraft of the Bureau of Mineral Resources carried out a low-level airborne radiometric survey in the Adelaide River, Brocks Creek, and McKinlay River areas of the Northern Territory. An area of 752 square miles was surveyed and 26 radiometric anomalies were located. The survey technique is described and the positions of the anomalies are shown on a map.
